programme.desc: In the 19th century, England controlled the biggest Empire the world had ever seen. Scientific breakthroughs, huge scale engineering, and great leaps in medicine led Britain's reign of global power. And yet, behind the facade there was a darkness. An unimaginable world of evil - theft, rape, murder and more. This was the real world of Jack the Ripper and Sherlock Holmes. But there was a lesser known killer on the loose who was far worse than any of the others, a woman who would succeed in becoming one of the world's most prolific serial killers. Her name was Amelia Dyer and she killed over 400 innocent babies. A seemingly gentle old lady, Amelia would take in children under the guise of nurturing and caring for them when in reality she starved and strangled them to death. Explore inconceivable recesses of humanity in this shockingly true story of human darkness and depravity at the turn of the century.

Anna is a young actress desperate to make it in the movies. She is invited to a series of filmed auditions, playing out various scenarios on camera. The problem is, the director is a perverted psychopath with only one thing on his mind. As Anna progresses through an ever more bizarre series of roles she slowly realizes that something is horribly wrong with this audition. Forced to strip and perform carnal acts in the name of the art, she eventually flips and takes matters into her own hands. A scenario many actresses may recognize in the industry, Scream Queen Killer is brutally realistic and superbly acted by Melanie Denholme (Lady of the Dark). How far is too far? programme.title: Travis Missouri rifle season nice buck
programme.desc: This by far was the toughest year we have had hot weather and rain, caused decreased deer movement. but persistence pays off for Travis he gets a awesome Missouri deer with a Alex Pro 6.5 Creedmoor on AR platform, shooting Fort Scott Munitions Tumble on impact solid coper bullets. Talk about internal damage it causes it for sure. The deer was chasing a doe in CRP field and Travis made a good 200 yard shot,

programme.title: Outhouse Buck
programme.desc: Todd was hunting the Missouri Rifle season about mid week of the season the weather was hot and rainy. It was not good hunting conditions, he had been out in the rain all morning and came in for lunch and the rain increased so they decided to take the night off and take a nap. Well one last look out the window before lying down showed deer in the field behind camp. after some glassing one was a nice buck, the chase is on. ended up taking a 200 yard shot with Alex Pro 450 Bushmaster shooting Fort Scott Munitions Tumble on Impact this combination was deadly and the recovery was easy. Hope you enjoy the video as much as we enjoyed making it.

programme.title: Pigs a different way
programme.desc: This was a pig hunt I will never forget. Fort Scott Munitions wanted to kill a pig with a 9mm cancel carry handgun. We tried from the blind but their was so many pigs we had a hard time getting to stand by himself in range. The second night we just put the hunter on top of the feeder sprayed him down with Scent Thief and waited. I was thinking filming from the blind this will never work then the feeder goes of scaring the crap out of the hunter, here comes the pigs. If you don't thinks a 9mm shot from a small handgun can kill a pig just watch. I hope you enjoy this video as much as we did making it. Hunt hard and often.

programme.title: Girls get it done.
programme.desc: Missouri rifle season the girls show us how its done. Shannon's wife Mindy kills her biggest buck yet. In a wild hunt that happened fast her excitement made her husbands hunt as well. Lindsey gets it done again, this time on opening day. She also kills a very nice buck on one of our clover plots. Lindsey self filmed this hunt and did amazing. What you wont see is Lindsey's buck was very hard to find the shot looked good and she was shooting a 450 Bushmaster, we did recover the deer thanks to Fort Scott Munitions. You can see on the video that the bullet hit part of the blind before reaching the deer and still did its job. I hope you enjoy we sure did. Hunt hard and often.

programme.title: Big Hogs and Dogs
programme.desc: All Seasons Pursuit and Fort Scott Munitions go on a Hog hunt what an amazing time. The first hunt on this video is a hunt with the dogs Ryan from Fort Scott gets to take a item off his bucket list. This was one of the coolest hunts I have been on good dogs and good people and dogs catch in the pond. This video was one of the best we had this season I thinks some very cool video shots. The second Hog hut on this video was from a blind with a 300 Blackout. and boy what a hog a lot of people say the 300 Blackout is not beg enough for hog but Fort Scott Munitions prove that wrong. I hope you enjoy this video as normal we had a blast. Hunt hard and often.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The episode opens with contestant Geoff Rempel sharing his powerful backstory and the unique challenges of competing without a military or firearms background—proving that heart, not just experience, earns a place on this team. As the mission begins, the team links up with Pete from Red Cat Drones to run light recon and test critical communication between ground and aerial support. Red Cat brings the best of the best to the skies while the team takes to the ground on bikes, learning to operate under pressure with real-time air-to-ground coordination. But it’s not all strategy and tech—emotions run high as contestant Hayley Taylor opens up about her late father and the personal mission driving her to push harder every day. From aerial coverage to cover stories, it’s not just about who’s strongest... it’s about who’s ready when it counts.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The day kicks off with a one-of-a-kind “hatting ceremony” as Don Mann is crowned—then quite literally set on fire. But there’s no time to admire the flames; Ken Shamrock is waiting with another round of punishing Lion’s Den training. With Iron Man training just one day away, the pressure is at an all-time high. Contestant Landon reflects on his past Surviving Mann experience, paying tribute to the mentors who guided him—and now stepping into that role himself. The countdown to mission time begins as gear is packed, coordinates plotted, and details roll in via Red Cat Drones. With the ISR team deployed, the first phase of the mission is underway. Every contestant must be ready to deliver their cover for status in an instant—because in this game, hesitation can be the difference between success and failure.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The path to mission readiness takes a sharp turn as contestants are introduced to the Cupolster—an innovative holster system that changes the game when seconds matter. Don delivers a critical safety lesson before the team puts the gear to the test, running a demanding course of fire from inside a truck. From standard draws to Cupolster drills, every move is about speed, precision, and survival under pressure. The action escalates with a SAR9 passenger-seat course of fire that leaves contestants breathless —proving that combat can come from anywhere, at any time. But the real trial begins when Ken Shamrock unleashes his legendary Iron Man challenge. In three-minute elimination rounds, contestants go toe-to-toe against each other, testing not only strength but everything they’ve absorbed under Shamrock’s punishing guidance. It’s survival of the fittest—where only the toughest, sharpest, and most disciplined will walk away victorious.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: Ken Shamrock’s Iron Man competition comes to a head as two contestants battle it out for the number one spot. Every strike, every takedown matters—because only one can walk away crowned the victor. But there’s no time to celebrate. It’s mission day. After a quick live-fire break, the team receives critical intel from the ISR daylight crew. The risk spikes as night falls and the mission is suddenly altered, forcing the contestants to adapt on the fly. With Red Cat providing coordination from above, the squad is redeployed under new marching orders and even higher stakes. A partially compromised team makes survival uncertain, but when the moment of truth arrives, the team leader takes decisive action—leading a direct breach on the target. One bold decision shifts the course of the mission entirely, and its success now hangs by a thread.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: With the mission complete, the contestants think the season is winding down—but HQ has other plans. Their once-fabricated cover story becomes reality, pulling them into a pulse-pounding new challenge designed to test strength, coordination, and mastery of weaponry. This hybrid competition pushes every skill to the limit, weeding out all but the most well-rounded tactical athletes. Along the way, the legendary Don Mann shares his own backstory, giving rare insight into the life and mindset of the man behind the mission. When the dust settles, only one competitor will rise above the rest—earning the title of the season’s most complete warrior.
